article.headline: NC A&amp,T 85, Campbell 60
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Five players scored in double figures to lead North Carolina A&T to an 85-60 win over Campbell on Friday afternoon in the Global Sports Classic in Las Vegas. Bruce Beckford led with 19 points and eight rebounds. Beckford was 8 of 8 from the field. Lamont Middleton also scored 19. Adrian Powell added 14 points. R.J. Buck, who was 3 of 3 from 3-point range, had 13 points, as did Jean Louisme. The Aggies (2-4), who led 43-29 at halftime, shot 60.8 percent from the field for the game and were 71 percent at the free throw line. Campbell shot 33.9 percent from the field for the game. Trey Freeman led the Fighting Camels (2-4) with 13 points and Darren White added 12. Antwon Oliver had six rebounds.
